<Project>
	<name>HAPS - Holistic Attack Prevention System</name>
	<homepage rdf:resource="http://stlab.istc.cnr.it/stlab/project/haps/" />
	<created>2018-06-12</created>
	<shortdesc xml:lang="en">
		The file contains the metadata about the software developed for Intrusion Detection.
		This metadata is published using DOAP Vocabulary (https://lov.linkeddata.es/dataset/lov/vocabs/doap)
		according to the FAIR principles (https://www.go-fair.org/fair-principles/). The repository of software
		contains an implementation of the state-of-the-art algorithms for intrusion detection using different
		Machine Learning Methods.
	</shortdesc>

	<description xml:lang="en">
		HAPS - Holistic Attack Prevention System is the project which aims at developing a software solution for
		automatic “cyber defense” of critical applications. The system will be able to predict information on
		possible vulnerabilities thanks to a learning component that will leverage (1) the source code of
		the target application (SAST metrics) and (2) the information generated during its use ( application
		log, network status, system status). The proposed approach, which pushes the state of the art of industrial
		solutions, aims to drastically improve the effectiveness of the SAST analysis by integrating it with information
		that is specific to the system under examination and therefore takes into account possible mitigation elements, already in place.
	</description>

